{#
   weather_tool.j2
   Prompt for the weather tool node.
   Instructs the agent how to use weather data
   to enrich its crop disease diagnosis.
   
   Variables:
   - location: string location name
   - weather_data: dict with weather details
#}

Weather data has been retrieved for: {{ location }}

Current conditions:
- Temperature: {{ weather_data.temperature }}°C
- Humidity: {{ weather_data.humidity }}%
- Wind speed: {{ weather_data.wind_speed }} km/h
- Rainfall last 7 days: {{ weather_data.rainfall }}mm
- Weather condition: {{ weather_data.description }}

Use this data to enrich your diagnosis:

{% if weather_data.humidity > 80 %}
⚠️ High humidity alert:
Conditions are highly favourable for fungal diseases
such as blight, mildew and leaf spot infections.
Increase suspicion of fungal disease causes.
{% endif %}

{% if weather_data.temperature > 35 %}
⚠️ Heat stress alert:
Temperatures above 35°C can cause heat stress symptoms
that mimic disease. Consider heat stress as a factor.
{% endif %}

{% if weather_data.rainfall > 50 %}
⚠️ High rainfall alert:
Excessive moisture increases bacterial disease risk
and can cause root rot symptoms in leaves.
{% endif %}

Factor these conditions into your diagnosis and
mention relevant weather risks in your response.